medical_history.chief_complaint: Lack of breast development and primary amenorrhea in a 17-year-old woman.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The patient sought medical attention at age 17. She had normal intelligence but exhibited Tanner stage I breast development and Tanner stage IV pubic hair despite normal external genitalia. The onset of symptoms (lack of breast development and amenorrhea) is linked to her normal pubertal development at age 11 but has shown no progress regarding menstruation.
medical_history.past_medical_history: The mother experienced normal pubertal development and reached menarche at age 11, had two pregnancies, regular menstrual cycles until menopause at age 49, and underwent hormone replacement therapy for 2 years thereafter.
